<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="378" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Tower</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-16"><hi rend="italic">December 16,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay directs Mr. Tower to ascertain discreetly what is intended by
                            warlike blockade without war, especially as regards neutrals, and to
                            represent the desirability of arbitration, which Venezuela now earnestly
                            wishes.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>